961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\" type=\"image/webp\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/EUsOzk26IMvzTNfBH3PElpZkk2A=/375x375/filters:format(webp)/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg, https://images.food52.com/HgexB_PkmS_4k5Ojucvvb2xc0uQ=/750x750/filters:format(webp)/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/JUvC_evybLk3BiVfYLzGI2-24X0=/375x375/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg, https://images.food52.com/6agh4mltszjscdvKYLAf5MHlyAI=/750x750/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg 2x\" alt=\"\" width=\"964\" height=\"964\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/JUvC_evybLk3BiVfYLzGI2-24X0=/375x375/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg, https://images.food52.com/6agh4mltszjscdvKYLAf5MHlyAI=/750x750/bb379f6f-f51a-445a-8393-1926ff961e5f--2022-0202_email_look-2-the-naturalist_gif-still_1x1_ty-mecham_1.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Ty Mecham\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003ch2\u003e4. Folded Napkins = Instant Upgrade\u003c/h2\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eNapkin folding sounds fussy, but it’s actually fun—and deceptively easy. This \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mOVJx-WnG9M\" target=\"_blank\"\u003elotus flower fold\u003c/a\u003e is a spring favorite of mine (and a guaranteed conversation starter).\nI always go for cloth over paper, and these \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/shop/products/7438-five-two-everyday-soft-cotton-napkins\"\u003eFive Two Cotton Napkins\u003c/a\u003e are the best. They’re soft, easy to wash, and come in spring-perfect hues that feel fresh without screaming “pastel.” Plus, the cotton feels a bit more relaxed.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n  \n\n\n              \u003ch2\u003e5. Add Water (And Wine!)\u003c/h2\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eOne of my OG table-setting memories is being in charge of filling water glasses with my cousin before big family dinners. It felt like an official duty—and it’s still a step I never skip.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eI like to set the table with full glasses \u003cem\u003ebefore\u003c/em\u003e guests arrive, and keep a pitcher on the table so no one has to get up mid-meal. For bigger dinners (six or more), add a second pitcher at the other end—along with a bottle of red and white, of course.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageInteraction\" data-ga-event-action=\"Pinterest Share\" data-ga-event-label=\"Article Body Image\" data-ga-destination-url=\"none\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 16.9 20.8\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16.8 6.3C16.5 3.2 13.6.4 10.1.1 4.8-.5.1 2.7 0 7.9c0 2.4.8 4 2.9 4.8 1.5-1.5-.3-2.4-.5-4C2 4.3 7.1.1 11.7 2.9c3.2 1.9 2.6 9.9-1.2 10.7-.8.1-1.8-.1-2.1-.5-1.9-1.8 1.5-4.8.4-7.3-.9-2.1-3.6-.4-3.9 1.5-.2 1 .3 2 .3 2.9 0 2.1-1.3 5-1.7 7.1-.2.9-.3 2.6-.1 3.4h1.5c1-1.6 1.6-4.1 2.1-6.3.3-.2.5.4.7.6 1.8 1.4 5 .6 6.4-.7 2.1-1.7 3-5.2 2.7-8\" fill=\"currentColor\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n      \u003c/a\u003e\n\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAO